04/06/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Chief Prosecutor Ina Rama submitted a report to parliament Tuesday (June 3rd) about criminal activity in 2007.
The document covers crimes linked to corruption, as well as crimes and violations committed by state and other public employees.
It concludes that, compared with 2006, the level of criminal activity increased by 11%.
The number of criminal proceedings against state employees climbed by 21%, and the number of corruption cases also increased significantly.
(Shqip, Gazeta Shqiptare, Shekulli - 04/06/08;
Top Channel - 03/06/08)
